Taking a look into management solutions for negotiating container sprawl within my homelab.
The problem keeps growing If you are a Docker fan, then this should be a treat! Think about how many times you've had to execute docker ps -a just to see a list of all the containers you have running on a given system. Now imagine you are maintaining several servers plus your main development rig&hellip;
Just within my homelab alone, there is a minimum of 30 containerized services, which wasn't too terrible to manage for awhile (although extremely tedious).
